DENVER AND RIO GRANDE WESTERN RAILROAD COMPANY v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6231. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Nov. 3, 1959. Grant H. Bagley and Grant Macfarlane, Jr., Salt Lake City, Utah, for appellant. A. Pratt Kesler, U. S. Atty., and William Jack Adams, Asst. U. S. Atty., Salt Lake City, Utah, for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed pursuant to written stipulation of counsel. D.C., 175 F.Supp. 662.
